Parwarish Episode 25 | Digitally Presented by Surf Excel , Vince Care, Mothercare &  VGOTEL | Aina Asif | Samar Jafri | Reham Rafiq | 1st JULY 2025 | ARY Digital Drama 

PARWARISH – The most-watched Pakistani drama of the season, Parwarish is a gripping tale of generational conflict, where love becomes control and independence feels like rebellion. As parents hold tight to cultural traditions and children chase dreams of freedom, misunderstandings shake the very foundation of the family. It’s a powerful reflection of the emotional battles playing out in households across Pakistan today.


Samar Jafri as Wali Jahangir:
Wali, the eldest son of Jahangir, is the emotional heart of Parwarish. Handsome, intelligent, and kind-hearted, Wali was raised in the freedom of America. He dreams of becoming a musician, but his father’s disapproval casts a long shadow. Now back in Pakistan, Wali must navigate a world where parental expectations and personal dreams collide, sparking the drama’s central conflict.

Aina Asif as Maya:
Maya, a bright and determined girl from a conservative, middle-class family, is ready to take on the world. Beautiful and self-assured, she aspires to become a doctor—a path her family supports only conditionally. Caught between love, ambition, and tradition, Maya embodies the struggle of many young women in today’s society.

Cast:
Samar Jafri as Wali Jahangir
Aina Asif as Maya
Naumaan Ijaz as Jahangir
Savera Nadeem as Mahnoor

Parwarish Episode 24 | Digitally Presented by Surf Excel , Vince Care, Mothercare &  VGOTEL | Aina Asif | Samar Jafri | Reham Rafiq | 30 June 2025 | ARY Digital Drama 

PARWARISH – The most-watched Pakistani drama of the season, Parwarish is a gripping tale of generational conflict, where love becomes control and independence feels like rebellion. As parents hold tight to cultural traditions and children chase dreams of freedom, misunderstandings shake the very foundation of the family. It’s a powerful reflection of the emotional battles playing out in households across Pakistan today.


Samar Jafri as Wali Jahangir:
Wali, the eldest son of Jahangir, is the emotional heart of Parwarish. Handsome, intelligent, and kind-hearted, Wali was raised in the freedom of America. He dreams of becoming a musician, but his father’s disapproval casts a long shadow. Now back in Pakistan, Wali must navigate a world where parental expectations and personal dreams collide, sparking the drama’s central conflict.

Aina Asif as Maya:
Maya, a bright and determined girl from a conservative, middle-class family, is ready to take on the world. Beautiful and self-assured, she aspires to become a doctor—a path her family supports only conditionally. Caught between love, ambition, and tradition, Maya embodies the struggle of many young women in today’s society.

snippet.description:
सरिताज किचनची सर्व उत्पादने शुद्ध, पारंपरिक आणि केमिकल विरहित आहेत.

आषाढ स्पेशल खुसखुशीत तिखट पुऱ्या | सहलीसाठी, महिनाभर टिकणारे तळणीचे धपाटे 2 चुका टाळा Dhapate Recipe
महिनाभर टिकणाऱ्या तिखट पुऱ्या | आषाढ स्पेशल तिखट मिठाच्या पुऱ्या रेसिपी | गव्हाच्या पिठाच्या तिखट पुऱ्या | तळणीच्या तिखट पुऱ्या | कापण्या धपाटे रेसिपी | तिखट पुऱ्या रेसिपी | धपाटे रेसिपी | आषाढ स्पेशल तळणीचे धपाटे रेसिपी | Ashadh special Tikhat mitachya purya recipe | gavhachya pithachya tikhat purya | talanichya tikhat purya | kapanya dhapate recipe | dhapate recipe | talaniche dhapate recipe |

एवढ्या प्रमाणात ५०-६० पुऱ्या होतात | measurements for 50-60 puri
साहित्य | Ingredients
 • लसूण पाकळ्या २०-२५ | Garlic cloves 20-25
 • हिरवी मिरची ५-६ | Green chilies 5-6
 • जिरे १ टीस्पून | Cumin seeds 1 tsp
 • ओवा १/२ टीस्पून | Carom seeds 1/2 tsp
 • गव्हाचे पीठ ३ कप | Wheat flour 3 cups
 • ज्वारीचे पीठ १ कप | Sorghum flour 1 cup
 • बेसन १/२ कप | Gram flour 1/2 cup
 • तेलाचे मोहन १/४ कप | Oil for shortening 1/4 cup
 • बारीक चिरलेली कोथिंबीर ३/४ कप | Finely chopped coriander leaves 3/4 cup
 • कसुरी मेथी १ टेबलस्पून | Dried fenugreek leaves 1 tbsp
 • पांढरे तीळ ३ टीस्पून | White sesame seeds 3 tsp
 • मीठ चवीनुसार | Salt to taste
 • हळद १/२ टीस्पून | Turmeric powder 1/2 tsp
 • तेल तळणीसाठी | Oil for deep frying

How to make tikhat mitachya purya | Ashadh Special Tikhat purya Recipe | How to make Ashadh special kapanya dhapate recipe
For the paste:To prepare the paste, take garlic, green chilies, cumin seeds, and carom seeds in a mixer jar and grind them to a paste.
To knead the puri dough:Now in a large mixing bowl, add wheat flour, sorghum flour, gram flour, and salt. Mix everything well.Heat the oil taken for shortening until it's very hot, and pour it over the flour mixture. First mix using a spoon, then rub it into the flour with your hands thoroughly.Now add the prepared paste, turmeric, white sesame seeds, chopped coriander, and dried fenugreek leaves. Mix well and knead into a stiff dough by adding a little water at a time.After kneading, apply a little oil on the dough and cover it for 10 minutes.
While rolling the puris:Roll one large roti (flatbread) and cut puris using a glass or tumbler, or roll small individual puris and keep ready for frying.
Frying the puris:Heat oil on medium flame. Once the oil is hot, add a few puris at a time (as many as the pan can hold). After adding, reduce the flame to medium and fry the puris well on both sides until crisp and golden.
Note:These puris are traditionally made during the month of Ashadha and served with raw mango pieces. Once cooled, they can be stored in an airtight container and will stay fresh for up to a month. They are a great option for travel or picnics.

snippet.title: The Coldest Village on Earth (Lost My Health for This Video) -71°C, -96°F
snippet.description:
Use the coupon code RUHI29 to buy the MyHeritage DNA kit for only $29/€29/£29 https://bit.ly/RuhiCenet_MH or start your family tree with a 14-day free trial.

Here is my friend's video:
Journey to the World's Coldest Village: Oymyakon at -71°C https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w6fyb46Z-SM
Don't forget to check out "The Ulengovs" channel: https://www.youtube.com/@TheUlengovs

Thanks to MyHeritage for sponsoring this video.

Imagine a village where temperatures drop as low as -71°C, -96°F. Here, spending just a few extra minutes outside can lead to frostbite, the loss of a limb, or even end of life.

I’m in the coldest inhabited place on Earth, at the coldest time of the year. This is Oymyakon. Just to stay alive, I’m wearing more than 20 layers of clothing, weighing nearly 14 kilos. Stepping outside from a warm 30°C home means facing a temperature drop of over 100 degrees. That’s why I’m also wearing gloves, boots, pants, and a coat, all made from reindeer fur. And even that’s not enough. And now, I’m about to show you what life is like when simply going outside becomes a battle for survival.

The cold doesn't just affect people and wild animals. It stops everything from functioning.  Phones don’t work properly and often shut down. Cars left outside freeze in just a few hours. Since the ground is always frozen, no fruits or vegetables can grow here.

We boarded a plane in Moscow, flying east for seven hours to Yakutsk. From there, we covered an 18 hour, 900 kilometer road trip. When we stepped out of the car, it felt like we were on another planet. The hairs in our nose were frozen, and we felt them prick with every breath. The dry air makes us cough uncontrollably.  

Oymyakon is home to around 800 people, spread across 1.5 square kilometers. Seeing anyone else outside is almost impossible, the village feels like it has been abandoned.

snippet.title: The CyberClash Is On! Clash of Clans New Season
snippet.description:
Corrupt megacorps and freedom-fighting Renegades battle for control of a neon-soaked dystopia! The CyberClash is on! Gear up with cybernetic Hero Skins and take a side in this battle of might and metal. Explore the Cyber Scenery and add some holographic hijinks to your Home Village. A whole host of epic Events and offers await this Season! 

Follow us on our Socials!
Twitter ► https://twitter.com/ClashofClans/
Instagram ► https://www.instagram.com/clashofclans 
Facebook ► https://www.facebook.com/ClashofClans 
TikTok ► https://www.tiktok.com/@clashofclans

Attack. Defend. Strategize. Download for free for mobile devices. supr.cl/PlayClashOfClans

From rage-­filled Barbarians with glorious mustaches to pyromaniac wizards, raise your own army and lead your clan to victory! Build your village to fend off raiders, battle against millions of players worldwide, and forge a powerful clan with others to destroy enemy clans.
PLEASE NOTE! Clash of Clans is free to download and play, however some game items can also be purchased for real money 

Also, under our Terms of Service and Privacy Policy, you must be at least 13 years of age to play or download Clash of Clans.
A network connection is also required.

FEATURES
- Build your village into an unbeatable fortress 
- Raise your own army of Barbarians, Archers, Hog Riders, Wizards, Dragons and other mighty fighters
- Battle with players worldwide and take their Trophies
- Join together with other players to form the ultimate Clan
- Fight against rival Clans in epic Clan Wars 
- Build 18 unique units with multiple levels of upgrades
- Discover your favorite attacking army from countless combinations of troops, spells, Heroes and Clan reinforcements 
- Defend your village with a multitude of Cannons, Towers, Mortars, Bombs, Traps and Walls
- Fight against the Goblin King in a campaign through the realm

Chief, are you having problems? Visit https://help.supercellsupport.com/clash-of-clans/en/

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

snippet.description:
Middle Class Baap Rajesh uncle comes on Fake Podcast and he is interviewed by Prashn Kumar on desi parenting, enjoy the funny Ride.

Download Astrotalk app here - https://chat.astrotalk.com/YbLv/SRD
First chat is free from my link

Fake Podcast | Season Finale – Middle Class Dad Unfiltered 
In this explosively funny finale, Prashann Kumar interviews the most iconic character of Indian households — the middle-class desi father. From love marriage vs arranged marriage, therapy jokes, toxic parenting, and Sonam-Raja-style honeymoon murder fears, to Parents Teacher Meetings slaps, privacy invasion, Instagram spying, and beating kids for spelling “chummi” wrong, this episode brutally exposes what it’s like growing up with a “traditional Indian dad.”

Whether you’re a college student, a working professional, a new-age parent, or just someone in therapy because of one – you’ll relate, and laugh out loud.


Performed by: Satish Ray, Abhishek Singh
Written by: Satish Ray, Abhishek Singh, Nitesh Tiwari
Cinematography and studio by: Magnality Films, Andheri West
Edited by: Omkar Bhalerao
Production: Omkar Bhalerao, Harsh Pandey
Creative Director: Nitesh Tiwari

snippet.title: Mangli Renuka Yellamma | Bonalu Song 2025 | Full Song | Suresh Bobbili | Indravathi | Nakka Srikanth
snippet.description:
🎶 MANGLI RENUKA YELLAMMA | BONALU SONG 2025 🎉
Celebrate the divine power of Renuka Yellamma with this energetic Bonalu 2025 anthem! Sung by the sensational Mangli and composed by the dynamic Suresh Bobbili, this song is a tribute to Telangana’s rich folk culture and the fierce goddess worshipped across the region.

Feel the spiritual energy rise as beats, devotion, and traditional Telangana folk vibes come alive in this electrifying song.


#mangli  #manglisongs #bonalusong2025  #manglibonalusongs #telanganabonalu #bonalunewsongs #nakkasrikanth #oggukatha #baindlakatha #renukayellammasongs
